// Subscripts, superscripts, and small capitals.
// Compile with:  typst compile main.typ out.pdf
#set page(width: 12cm, height: auto, margin: 1.5cm)
#set text(font: "Libertinus Serif", size: 12pt)

Chemistry sits below the baseline: water is H#sub[2]O and
carbon dioxide is CO#sub[2].

Physics sits above it: E = mc#super[2], and the
1#super[st], 2#super[nd], and 3#super[rd] place.

Small capitals set a name or an acronym at the height of lowercase
letters: #smallcaps[The United Nations] was founded in 1945, and
its charter mentions #smallcaps[unesco].
